{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Job|14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","chapter":14,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":1,"text":"Anyone born of woman is short of days and full of trouble.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":2,"text":"He blossoms like a flower, then withers; he flees like a shadow and does not last.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":3,"text":"Do you really take notice of one like this? Will you bring me into judgment against you?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":4,"text":"Who can produce something pure from what is impure? No one!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":5,"text":"Since a person’s days are determined and the number of his months depends on you, and since you have set limits he cannot pass,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":6,"text":"look away from him and let him rest so that he can enjoy his day like a hired worker.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":7,"text":"There is hope for a tree: If it is cut down, it will sprout again, and its shoots will not die.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":8,"text":"If its roots grow old in the ground and its stump starts to die in the soil,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":9,"text":"the scent of water makes it thrive and produce twigs like a sapling.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":10,"text":"But a person dies and fades away; he breathes his last —where is he?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":11,"text":"As water disappears from a lake and a river becomes parched and dry,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":12,"text":"so people lie down never to rise again. They will not wake up until the heavens are no more; they will not stir from their sleep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":13,"text":"If only you would hide me in Sheol and conceal me until your anger passes. If only you would appoint a time for me and then remember me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":14,"text":"When a person dies, will he come back to life? If so, I would wait all the days of my struggle until my relief comes.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":15,"text":"You would call, and I would answer you. You would long for the work of your hands.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":16,"text":"For then you would count my steps but would not take note of my sin.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":17,"text":"My rebellion would be sealed up in a bag, and you would cover over my iniquity.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":18,"text":"But as a mountain collapses and crumbles and a rock is dislodged from its place,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":19,"text":"as water wears away stones and torrents wash away the soil from the land, so you destroy a man’s hope.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":20,"text":"You completely overpower him, and he passes on; you change his appearance and send him away.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":21,"text":"If his sons receive honor, he does not know it; if they become insignificant, he is unaware of it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Job:14:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Job","bookOrder":17,"chapter":14,"verse":22,"text":"He feels only the pain of his own body and mourns only for himself.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{